Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Peel and grate the @garlic{3}.

On a lined #baking tray{}, rub the @Irish chicken breast{320%g} with @Thai style spice mix{1%sachet}, @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Sprinkle over the @sesame seeds{1%sachet}.

Cook on the top shelf, ~{25-30%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and equipment after handling raw chicken. Chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.
> TIP: Notice a stronger smell from your chicken? This is normal due to packaging used to keep it fresh.

Meanwhile, pour 300ml cold salted @water{to taste} into a #medium pot with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and bring to the boil.

Once boiling, lower the heat to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{12%minutes}, then remove the #pot from the heat.

Keep covered for another ~{12%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Trim the tip of the @broccoli{1}. Cut head into small florets and stem into 2cm pieces.

Zest and quarter the @lime{1}.

Place a #pan over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the broccoli for ~{2-3%minutes}, add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Add a splash of @water{to taste} and cover with a #lid or some #foil{}. Cook until tender, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Once cooked, transfer the broccoli to a #bowl{} and cover to keep warm.

Return the pan to medium-high heat.

Add 75ml water (double for 4p), @red Thai style paste{1%sachet}, @ketjap manis{1%sachet} and @honey{2%sachet}.

Bring to the boil and cook until reduced by half, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Once reduced, remove from the heat.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop the sachet in a bowl of hot water for ~{1%minute}.

Stir @butter{1%tbsp} into the sauce.

Season to taste with @salt{to taste}, @pepper{to taste} and a squeeze of lime juice.

Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if required.

Once cooked, stir the lime zest through the rice, fluffing it up as you go.

Share the zesty lime rice between bowls.

Top with the sesame chicken, spooning over the sauce from the pan.

Serve the broccoli alongside.

Place any remaining lime wedges on the side for squeezing over.